comments.body: @hackartisan The structure used in this instance assumes future ingests as these are patron requests of a single roll from a multi-roll collection. These four are the only four that didn't ingest from a larger bulk ingest that included multiple reels. All other ingests went through, so it appears that these ingests are the the only MVW ingests that are trying to go as single volumes.

Figgy is interpreting the numbers of the subdirectories as alma IDs. It interprets any number greater than 4 digits as an alma ID. If you want to get these in while we work on updating figgy, changing those subdirectory names should make it work.
